CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 11, 1945, pg. 13, reads: "Feast of the Frogs - Mrs. William G. Nunn, wife of the The Courier's manager editor, had a fully laden board at her table.  Mrs. Nunn's sister, Mrs. Sybil Laney, and Mrs. Mary Nunn, the Courier editor's mother, helped dish out the food as admiring friends looked on.  Left to right, rear row: Mrs. Wilbert Holloway, Mrs. Ira Cornelius and daughter, Mrs. Jeanne Deck, Mrs. Esther Bolden and Mrs. Antonie Edwards.  The Wave, seated at table, is Miss Clementine Forsythe. - All Photos By Harris."
TitMainTitle: Women, including Mrs. Nunn, Sybil Laney, Mary Nunn, Mrs. Wilbert Holloway, Mrs. Ira Cornelius, Jeanne Deck, Esther Bolden, Antoine Edwards, and Clementine Forsythe gathered around table with food at FROGS picnic, South Park
